      • CommandSettings

        public CommandSettings(java.lang.String prefix,
                       net.dv8tion.jda.core.JDA jda)
        This is the constructor. The parameters are validated automatically. In case of any problems, this will throw an IllegalArgumentException.
        Parameters:
        jda - Put your active JDA here. This is important for the activation of the CommandListener.
        prefix - The String you will have to put before every command in order to get your command execution registered.

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public CommandSettings add(java.lang.String label,
                           ICommand command)
        This method is used to add commands from your project. Every command which is supposed to be active should be added by this.

        The two parameters will be put in a HashMap which is used by the API to notice commands.

        Parameters:
        label - The label which describes your command, i.e. the string after the prefix [prefix][label]
        command - An instance of your command class which implements ICommand.
        Returns:
        The current object. This is to use fluent interface.

      • activate

        public void activate()
        Sets the prefix and the command HashMap for the rest of the API.

        Note that you shouldn't create new CommandSettings and activate them after having already activated one. This can cause problems. To "save" your settings, this is important, because otherwise your commands won't be registered.
